# UPower Hardware DB addon that fixes Logitech MX keyboard showing up as a mouse
#
# References
#  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/upower/upower/-/issues/128
#  https://github.com/systemd/systemd/blob/aed42a4b4daf396ed528b29efbf41d1ad6a856d2/hwdb.d/60-input-id.hwdb

## Instructions
# 1. Copy this file to /etc/udev/hwdb.d/ folder
# 2. sudo systemd-hwdb update
# 3. sudo udevadm trigger /dev/input/event*
# 4. Preferably restart machine

# Register Logitech MX Keys
id-input:modalias:input:b0003v046Dp408Ae0111*
 ID_INPUT_MOUSE=0
